My meme

After finishing a first stage computer science course last year, I thought I was a semi-professional programmer until I saw the content in friend’s third stage computer science class.

library(magick)

# Find the pictures for the meme.
scary_dino = image_read("https://d.newsweek.com/en/full/2198248/dinosaur-found-china.webp?w=790&f=99f4156a3682f908e59963cbe2ca9f12")%>%
  image_resize("200x200")
google_dino = image_read("https://dino-chrome.com/static/images/dino.jpg")%>%
  image_resize("200x200")

#Write the content of the left part of meme
text1 = image_blank(width = 200,
                    height = 60,
                    color = "#ffffff")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "I think my \nprogramming level is ",
                 color = "#000",
                 size = 15,
                 font= "mono",
                 gravity = "center")

# Create the left part 
left_part = image_append(c(text1, scary_dino),stack = TRUE)

#Write the content of the right part of meme
text2 = image_blank(width = 190,
                    height = 60,
                    color = "#FFFFFF")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "IN FACT",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 25,
                 font= "mono",
                 gravity = "south")

# Create the right part
right_part = image_append(c(text2, google_dino),stack = TRUE)

# Create the title
title = image_blank(width = 425,
                    height = 60,
                    color = "#ffffff")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "When I overcome a bunch of obstacles \nand the code runs successfully",
                 color = "brown",
                 size = 20,
                 font= "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

meme = image_append(c(left_part,right_part))

# Create and export the meme
finalp = image_append(c(title,meme),stack = TRUE)
finalp
image_write(finalp, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

When I was told to make a gif, the only idea was to make a continuous image, and I think the animal running posture is beautiful.
